'''''4 Soccer Simulators''''' (later also released as '''''Pro Soccer Simulator''''') is a collection of four [[association football|soccer]] [[video game]]s developed and released by [[Codemasters]] in 1988. It included four games; ''11-a-Side Soccer'',<ref>[http://www.gametap.com/video-games/11-A-Side-Soccer-20000667-16.html 11-a-Side Soccer] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091111000628/http://www.gametap.com/video-games/11-A-Side-Soccer-20000667-16.html |date=2009-11-11 }} at gametap.com</ref> ''Indoor Soccer'', ''Soccer Skills'' and ''Street Soccer''. The games are all played using vertical scrolling.<ref>[http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/articles/foursoccersims.htm 4 Soccer Sims] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514203441/http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/articles/foursoccersims.htm |date=2011-05-14 }} at ysrnry</ref> The collection was released on [[ZX Spectrum]], [[Amstrad CPC]], [[IBM PC compatible|PC]], [[Nintendo Entertainment System]] and [[Commodore 64]]. It was also advertised for [[Atari ST]] and [[Amiga]] but these versions were never released.<ref>[http://hol.abime.net/1157/miscshot ''Pro Soccer Simulator''] at ''Hall of Light''</ref>

